## 3.7 Data model (Switch Kit)
### `switch_requests`
- `id` uuid pk
- `property_id` uuid fk
- `customer_id` uuid fk
- `category_key` text
- `sku_id` uuid (target service)
- `requested_start_date` date
- `start_cycle_id` uuid (or derived)
- `status` enum (DRAFT/PENDING_START/READY_TO_SCHEDULE/ACTIVE/PAUSED/CANCELLED/FAILED)
- `selected_level_id` uuid (defaulted + editable)
- `answers` jsonb (guidance questions)
- `access_notes` text
- `photo_urls` text[]
- `created_at`, `updated_at`

### `switch_events` (optional event log)
- `switch_request_id`
- `event_type` (created, confirmed, postponed, activated, cancelled, failed)
- `payload` jsonb
- `created_at`

RLS:
- customer can only read/write their own switch requests
- providers cannot access
- admin full access

